Art Basel notes year 12 (spoiler the notes are shockingly the same every single year) 

- never wear heels to the beach, no matter how cute your outfit is you’ll look like a dummy when you fall over in the sand. 

- the contemporary art here inspires the entire culture it attracts, saturating south beach with stimulating branded experiences and bold style choices, which completely shift how people talk about creativity 

- this is the only place you’ll see ceos, emerging artists, professional athletes, slick grifters, celebrities, playing in one room

- Kim Kardashian looks prettier and smaller than any real human being, I’m starting to question if she’s been replaced by a robot.
First Hanukkah, third pizza oven fail, fortieth wedding dress attempt, 16th year of laying around and doing nothing but also everything with these two @megjo_e & @jcnewmark
should we try that whole Roaring 20’s thing again?

48 hours at @etthemstockholm… it has such a strong sense of place, no sense of time, and the full embodiment of being at the home (with the kitchen @etthemfood) you didn’t know you dreamt of. ❤️ 10/10

This all started with a Pandemic purchase.  On one of the long, grey winter nights I haphazardly bought an Aurora Borealis light projector off Amazon.  We used to have pandemic picnics where we would lay down under the lights and dream about the universe. 

Fast forward to this Christmas, @grant_achatz gave me the projector in its beat up Amazon box.  Ever the optimist and lover of thoughtful gifts, I thought he was just being cute and wanted to lay down and dream under the lights at home, I was totally happy with the sentiment. But that wasn’t it. 

It came attached to papers that had booked a trip to go see the Aurora Borealis at a place called @loggerslodge in Swedish Lapland, a luxe lodge for 2. I think I immediately shed a tear over what has become his specialty: over the top gifts that are thoughtful beyond measure. 

But honestly, nothing about flying 13+ hours, multiple flights, then driving 90 minutes to get 50km away from the Arctic Circle where the average temperature is below zero to a remote cabin in the woods sounded… ideal. But holy hell was I wrong. 

Snow mobiling across frozen lakes. Swedish saunas. Husky sledding through hills and forests. Arctic berry and herb foraging. Reindeer sledding. Reindeer feeding. Reindeer eating. Lassoing reindeer (I could talk for hours about the emotional rollercoaster of the reindeer farms). Star gazing in a jacuzzi surrounded by snow. Northern Light chasing. Meeting the Sami people, the indigenous culture of Lapland. Hearing lore about trolls and reindeer trophy ears in a teepee. Cooking lunches over open fires in the snow. Spending time with two kindred spirits who have dedicated their lives to opening a small lodge where no detail has been spared and sharing their thirst for adventure with the guests who are lucky to stay there. 

So many friends have said this is a “bucket list trip” and that has actually inspired us to come up with our own Bucket List (so far there isn’t much on it so I would love some suggestions on your brain altering destinations please!). 

And if you need a Sweden itinerary - I’ve got you. ❤️🇸🇪

🕺🏻🪩

Grant didn’t touch the dance floor and Rachel ripped her dress in half immediately (good thing I had a backup!) but after that, we were dancing queens. #peskowritz
White Lotus, white wardrobes, white-hot luck.

A final scroll through the #peskowritz wedding week to remember. Guess we should start planning ours now!🙈❤️ so far my list includes comfort food, Rihanna, aliens, spy craft, 15 outfit changes, and a really big boat. What else do we need? 😌

New York Minute: 

- Reunited & delighted with @foodiemagician, brain exploding when he pulls a folded card out of his wallet that is the number I chose and had my old dog’s name written on it. Still convinced magic is witchcraft, there is no other answer. 

- First selfie back at the @rosewoodthecarlyle & @bemelmansbar since my spontaneous “I’m moving to LA” 2018 party 

- Cuddles with my nephews baby Bert & @erniehemi, but actually just trying to get some of their elite meals 

- The outlandishly priced potato at Caviar Kaspia 

- Sidewalk classic: Smoking a joint writing an eloquent complaint about said dinner 

- Short girl syndrome: tucked into the fireplace seats at @jacsonbondny (RIP Smile Cafe) after giving up on a mean game of pool where Mohar just made up all her own rules 

- A spiritually healing home made grilled cheese 

- Feeling relevant by getting into @thenines_nyc instead of just @acme_nyc

Not pictured by HIGHLY RECOMMEND: feast over the best brunch ever @donangienyc; visit the hyper maximalist @sabyasachiofficial store for creative inspo; walk through a 150 year old door and pick up a rare cookbook at Joanne Hendricks Cookbooks in Tribecac meet Joanne who is an absolute dream; sit in the dreamy pink Parisian lobby @fouquets.newyork

Palm Beach first timer🏝️:

Grab a matcha and admire the intricately hand-painted pastel wallpapers of @thecolonypalmbeach. That’s right, Hand. Painted. Jungle. Scenes. 🤯 Also 10/10 people watching by the garden pool. 

Pick your jaw off the floor at @thebreakers, modeled off the opulent Villa Medici in Rome and quite literally the foundation of the Gilded Age in America. I broke my neck whipping between the facades of the marble ballrooms and the facelifts on the 90 year old clientele. 

Explore the famous @worthavenuepalmbeach antique stores and hidden alley specialty shops, whose walls hold rare art, unseen Cartier collections, and other unimaginable tokens like this silver flamingo - each hair is a hand placed piece of metal - yours for a mere $250,000. Bonus: the long term shop keepers have STORIES. 

Do not miss having a delightful & decadent meal @buccanpalmbeach. Chefs kiss. 

Then put on your final pastel sundress to walk great halls of the @flaglermuseum mansion and a little shopping fix at the @theroyalpoincianaplaza 

I also inserted a day @thebocaraton (and their epic 50,000 sq ft spa) with @laurellejade before she welcomes in two twin baby boys, reminding ourselves “we don’t have heads shaped for hats”. 

After a quick 3 days my biggest fear started to seep in…Am I a Florida girl now? 🤩

LA 🌞 March 🌴diary 

Late night stress eating waffle fries alone @1hotels planning surprises for the girlfriends who usually help me plan my surprises… 

Refining my 24k gold and espresso dark chocolate cake skills, shooting with sugar maverick @thecaker. 

Waiting for the lidocaine to hit @facileskin because “I’m a huge baby”. 

Shedding & rebalancing with a @annaowsian_yoga private sound bath with my mysterious women @jane_lerman @christinalperez @atcodinha 

Meeting up with very important media moguls “after work” (a solid 1pm). 

Squishing my #sadbeigebaby fairy godson Callum Grey. 

Ordering 1 of every menu item at Hollywood’s actually authentic taco stands with @iamsilentdan. The signs were hand painted and everything was $4 so I knew this would be fire. 

Taking it as a sign that the same day we chose a snake motif for our wedding the #BulgariSerpenti 75th Anniversary shop opens. 

Sneaking selfies at @therow while @rach_anastasia is trying to not to have a panic attack over seeing @instadanjlevy. 

Said surprise from slide 1, my bridesmaid proposal boxes that gave me 2 days of dopamine and TikTok fame.

new york minutes ❤️

Spent 75% of my time wedding dress shopping but no spoilers here. nyc got its own bean and it sure did bean 🫘. favorite things about returning to the city that still feels like home 1) immediately getting sushi 🍣 dear god someone send good fish to chicago 2) exploring stores / spaces that have become design destinations. of note: @khaite_ny, @amnh and 3) turning myself around a dozen times and not even being upset about it. 4) what is becoming a favorite pastime: early mornings with @alexandrafitz and late nights with @andy, both perched amongst their immaculate collection of chairs. 5) if weather permits, which it so kindly did, getting a slice of pepperoni, smoking a joint, and meandering my way slowly across town.

Happy 18 years Alinea! 🎂

There was a certainly a lot to celebrate this week.  Grant’s birthday is April 25 but Alinea’s is May 4, and each year he finds the latter more significant. 18 years and he’s still pulling 16 hour days sometimes 6 days a week 👊🏼. We spent his day at our wedding venue (!) and came home to visitors @allisonparc @clintob, toasting her bday and their own beautiful union 💍 . In a stroke of luck, we were just in time for Alinea’s new Spring Menu, a tightly choreographed transformation they haven’t executed since pre-pandemic 2019. Injected with new whimsy and wonder, here are a few items from the ~30 courses: 

1/ Fever dream florals & ferns by @igniteglass, including colored calla lily bowls. When @grant_achatz saw me walk through the door, he swapped mine out with one that matched my outfit. Details! 

2/ The lilies contained a Grilled Garden Gazpacho Slushie, fire charred ingredients gave the cold slushy a smokey aroma before they were pureed, macerated for a day, frozen with Nitrous Oxide, and drizzled with charred olive oil. 

3/ Salad Paintbrush: Who needs a fork when you can tie your spring veggies like pea tendrils, fennel fronds, and dandelions around a twig? We swept the brooms in a caramelized raspberry vinaigrette and macadamia nut butter. 

4/ @regiisova Osetra Caviar on a dish designed to mimic the texture. Paired with a mussel, vanilla, peppercorn, lychee tapioca pudding with champagne gelee. Chef’s kiss! 

5/ Head & Tails: We fished out Australian Tiger Prawns from a forest of hot seaweed and laid them in a wildly complex Japanese crumble bed. Paired with shrimp head stock syrup and mounted with a creamy tomato paste shrimp shell butter. 

6/ Squeaker: squab, potpourri, blueberry, foie gras, aigre-doux. 

7 / “it’s yogurt” jameed

8/ Australian raised Wagyu sous vide short ribs, spiced pomegranate sauce, poached asparagus, rhubarb ribbon. 

9 & 10/ After our last savory, @Allisonparc whispered “I smell banana in the air” and I lovingly, rolled my eyes. Shame on me because 10 mins later she was right, they had scented the air with banana to introduce a banana split themed table dessert! Floating Balloons to close.

In the heart of NYC's swirling storm,
Thriving souls find their vibrant form.

Amidst the chaos, dreams take flight,
A symphony of life, day and night.

Creative souls reach, dreams intertwine,
In this eccentric jungle, we redefine.

BIG WEEK FOR FRIENDS AND FAM: 
Home girl got a wedding dress; Allie opened a Galerie! Cyndi & Adam opened a bar; Ashli adopted a chipmunk; Jax and Tolga crowned kings of nightlife; and CP and i redecorated a house. BUSY LIL 🐝 in my safe space

Dominican Republic 🏝️ @casadecampodr is a place where film develops like it’s the 1970’s, where you meet 🐴 horses named Helen and Robert,🐱 where dozens of wild kittens eat right out of your hand, where the 🌮 tacos are fire, the conversation is loving 🥰 , where girls poop rainbows 🌈 and tropical rains fall down everywhere except above your swimming pool 🏊‍♀️. Perfect place for sprinkling @rach_anastasia with birthday joy 🥳 and a comforting backdrop to match the Barbados set for the devastating Succession series finale.

36 Hours in a 100 degree Austin heat wave and I’m hooked (as you can see by my newly acquired @tecovas ivory cowboy boots). I very quickly learned that a city who pursues creative expression through food, is a city full of happy friendly people. 

Want to be sure to note two amazing dinners at @esteatx and @birdiesaustin, who both went above and beyond to accommodate for our somewhat complicated food restrictions.  Two non-drinkers, one with a citrus allergy and one with a spicy-food sensitivity are probably the two saddest things to say to a Texan (no limes? No jalapeños? No tequila? Are you sure?) but we were welcomed with open arms and delicious food. If you manage to get a table at #EsteAustin, be sure to order the Trout a la pulla and fish tacos, and I would commit crimes for the chilled corn soup at #BirdiesAustin. 

Of course none of that mattered at our meat-centric next stop @FranklinBBQ (yes its worth the hype) where we shared a picnic table with the @nixtataqueria team (for our next trip) and basically drank a mountain of fall off the bone, juicy as hell brisket, spare ribs, pulled pork, turkey, sausage, and pecan pie in 110 degree heat. 

We stayed at the new @sohohouse Austin (gigantic rooms with all the good stuff - full size bath products, standalone copper tubs, @dyson hair tools, and a relaxing rooftop pool) on South Congress and it put us within arm’s reach of very good quick snacks: fish & chips @perlassouthcongress (where we met a bartender who staged at Alinea in 2014!) the rainbow salad @joannsaustin; and an astrology inspired @amysicecreams that melted within 2 minutes but was quite delicious. 

And if my trip couldn’t get any more Texas, a Dallas friend reached out with a young woman in need of a shm-shmortion and the dystopian feeling of women not being able to get access to reproductive care while my boots were on the ground in Texas was deeply felt. Crediting @teafund @theafiyacenter @plancpills @plannedparenthood with support resources here. For legal reasons, this part is fiction. 

Thank you to our lovely hosts @madein @chip_malt and @marcellamalt this would not have been the same without your expert guidance! 🤠👢🌵🥵

According to my #astrocartography chart, my Descendant and Neptune lines go right through Los Angeles. 

🔮 The Neptune line points out “a place where I will be more likely to lead a more contemplative, spiritual lifestyle (can you tell by this caption) as the border between the subtle and material planes are most blurred for me here. Boundaries disappear and the world becomes more dreamlike.” Confirmed. 

🌙 The Descendant line - at the horizon, where the cosmos and the earth melt together and the real “You” is revealed - makes this a “place where I will find strong support and understanding in others, especially through love.” Confirmed. 

Maybe it’s because we fell in love here. Maybe it’s because our dearest friends are here. Maybe it’s because when people hate on it, it just magnifies how ugly they are on the inside. Or maybe it’s just because of the normalized Non-Alcoholic and tinned fish menu options, idk. LA was will always have a little piece of my soul.

☀️ 🌴🤍😌

Things I learned at the beach: 

🌊 When in LA, go @bliss.beach or go home. 
🎲 The brass dice game of Farkle is incredibly fun.
🏖️ You can just dig a hole and pee in it, especially if you’re surrounded by polka dot umbrellas.
👒 When it comes to straw hats, bigger the better. 
🍣 DIY sushi hand roll kits make a brilliant dinner party
😌 Surround yourself with people who ground you.

The love I feel from this human is bigger than all the fireworks in  the whole sky. ❤️🇺🇸 🎆

Also never throwing another party without a bubble machine, a pizza oven, and 5 off duty chefs to keep an inappropriate amount of food coming for hours…

Enter: French Nobility Era. 1/2

Versailles, @airelleschateaudeversailles which included full Louis XIV era costuming, food, activities, and 2 private tours of the Hall of Mirrors.

I learned a lot about the French nobles, the deeply traditional and strict royal customs (the public birth! the social climb! the peasant cosplay!), and the out of touch lifestyles that led to the downfall of the monarchy. Regardless of who was on what side of history, the impressive artistry, craftsmanship, and architectural feats developed here are undeniable. 🤯

Au revoir Versailles! Photo dump  2/2. 
 
1 - continuing to honor the French in @jgalliano 
2 - fact checking Sofia Coppola’s Marie Antoinette after a Sun King massage 
3 - being captivated by the ever changing wildflowers from the grounds 
4 - riding an electric boat ride in the Grand Canal, which soon ran out of juice and we had to do some serious rowing. If so desired, a butler will bring you a picnic in a vintage basket 
5 - the beginning of the Michelin-starred Grand Feast by @alainducasse, a formal candlelit dinner with all the traditional pomp of the time 
6 - Twirling in the Hall of Mirrors 
7 - Jet lag caviar & French fry terrace service 
8 - The velvet couch lined underground pool 
9 - A globe holding champagne cocktail fixings 
10 - The glowing faces of two extremely happen, soft skinned @valmontcosmetics die hard fans.

3 Days in the Douro Valley: Since my nemesis, the relentless lemon 🍋, had snagged me again with another set of itchy face rashes 🥵, the slow pace of the @sixsensesduorovalley was welcomed with open arms. 

Within hours we had mastered the art of unhurried movement: ☀️ 97 degree days spent in cold pools with 🍨 gelato, regular visits to the widely undervalued 🍷 wine-by-the-glass vending machine (business idea… 💡) and 🍝 languid 3 hour meals, all outside with a vista.  @Rach_anastasia and I roped up with an arborist/karate master, to ascend ancient trees of a 🌳 forest planted as a gift from a husband to his wife 500 years ago; @Grant_achatz befriended his doggle-ganger, the house 🐕 🦊 dog Foxie, who led us down a secret vineyard path (and who opened up the endless ‘are we dog people?’ and ‘are we vineyard people?’ conversations). And after roaming the streets of a nearby village  we ditched our 🛶‘cultural boat tour’ to spend a few more hours truly on vacation, eating French fries, sipping aperitivo, overanalyzing our well being, and enjoying the refreshing embrace of water 🏊‍♂️🌊 

A triumphant weekday I think.

👰🏻‍♀️🚿 I’ve come to learn that a wedding is just as much about you marrying your partner as it is about you building the village that is going to support you through the rest of your lives. 

And as much it pains me to not have been a part of the mood boarding, color scheming, zoom hangouts, excessive online shopping, and menu planning, @rach_anastasia @jane_lerman and @valoriedarling couldn’t have made me feel more loved by surprising me with all my favorite things: friends and family, tarot readings, committed *branding* and decor, cakes, cookies, flowers, sunshine, an entire non-citrus menu, and connected conversation. 

I’m pinching myself today to make sure this all wasn’t just a dream. 💕🥹👰🏻‍♀️

Also truly cannot thank @valoriedarling enough for being an insanely wonderful friend who always captures our big life moments and is truly one of the most talented photographers out there!!!

Wellness & witchcraft, what else can I girl ask for? 

Life threw some really big curveballs my way this season, and planning a bachelorette party was not in the cards. But turns out that real friends will know what’s best for you (in this case squeezing in 3 days of total surprises), they will go above and beyond to make magical memories, and they will let you know that it’s ok to lean on each other when you’re too tired to do everything yourself. They will also be flexible when you have an allergic reaction in the middle of the weekend and have to shift gears into a sunglasses at night game night at home. 

Shoutout to the worlds best bridesmaids who planned this mini-bach weekend in a matter of days and somehow surprised me with the perfect events at every turn. @rach_anastasia @valoriedarling @jane_lerman Idk what I would do without you! 💕💕💕
Words cannot express how magically kismet having a  witch themed bachelorette party before Halloween is! From magical manifestations to spiritual alignments, 11/11 cannot come soon enough!

🥹 35mm barefoot Valentino and more snaps from the bridal shower. ❤️

Halloween but you’re getting married. 

🌝 a Full Moon, 🌚 a Lunar Eclipse, 🧘‍♀️ a sound bath, 🧙 spellcasting with personalized potions, and 2 of Chicago’s trademark events: 💃🏼 burlesque in a basement speakeasy & a house music 🕺 dance party. 

The costume: Cosmic Enchantress Bride 👰🏻‍♀️ and her Aviary 😉 of ravens (aka a 🐦‍⬛ rave of ravens at a rave). We even had a magical cake and carried a little bird dubbed Grant around with us all night (minus a few moments where @sundownd & @michtahi had to eyelash glue his wing back on #9) 

Happy Halloween! The countdown begins! ❤️
And to think it’s just the beginning. ❤️

Favorite pre-wedding memory: waiting for @grant_achatz in the back alley of Alinea late at night and driving across town to take dance lessons with @mj_hawks 🥹❤️ TBD on if I can post the blooper reel… 😏

The Love Potion. 

The first step in our wedding invitation design started from where so many of our conversations do: experience.  We knew we wanted to give our guests a gift, and what better suited for a wedding than A Love Potion. 

And this is where the creative magic between us begins - we go down a research rabbit hole of ingredients that inspire love (hibiscus for allure, raspberry for love, etc), and because @grant_achatz can’t make a normal cocktail, we made an 8 step Love Potion that included infused salt rims, incense bundles, and the most important step before the sip “look into each other’s eyes and give a heartfelt compliment.” 

The boxes and paper goods were designed by our incredible collaborator Courtney from @cecilespaperco, who every day would take our creative inspiration and translate it through her art. She even took photos I snapped from our first trip to Merida and hand illustrated the jungle print from actual things from the hotel (minus the jaguar, that’s a spirit animal bestowed upon us by a Shaman). 

These were truly a labor of blood, sweat, and love - @grant_achatz and @micahmelton made 80 lbs of cocktail TWICE (due to one very bad UPS liquid explosion) and Grant nearly lost a finger hand making 100 incense bundles. But the joy it brought to every one of our guests was worth every sliced finger and broken package. 

The tequila based cocktail was also served at the wedding, and truly was such a delicious and beautiful way to bring us closer to our family and back into the jungle. ❤️

The Pool Day! ☀️🌊🌮 

This morning started with a heart opening cacao and reiki ceremony by my dear @lo_mcgrath @saltspellbeauty. It was a quiet moment of grounding, where we set intentions of love, connection, and presence for the day. 

Shortly after wrapping myself in a silk scarf featuring our wedding wallpaper print, the dream team @lo.mcgrath @marianamcgrathmakeup @taramaiettastyle sewed 64 baroque South Sea pearls from the Philippines — a nod to my home culture and love for mermaids — into my hair. Huge credit to @karlinbergum making this custom piece come to life. 

Our mission for the day was to channel the indulgent leisure of a 1970’s Slim Aaron’s Acapulco Pool Party, but in the Yucatan jungle. Grant and I were serenaded into the party by a traditional mariachi band, and we met our guests for a day full of of ceviche, cerveza, massage stations, margaritas, fresh guacamole and taco stations, and of course a cart of sweet nieves and paletas (fruity ice treats) to cool down. 

What our florist @sirenfloralco did with palms and coconuts was nothing short of a modern jungle transformation, and thankfully my planners @lyndenlane convinced me that “yes, we do have to replaces all the towels, umbrellas, cushions, tableware, and floaties” with our dusty ocean palette. My favorite touch: a vintage polaroid camera with Stay Focused written in sharpie on the counter capturing special moments.

📸 @abigaillewisphoto @vinuthnagaridipuri

The Welcome Dinner
 
Earthly Indulgence + Celestial Wonder were the themes for night 1 of our Yucatan Jungle wedding. Travel days for us require creature comforts -  great food, cozy spaces, deep chats - and we wanted just that for our guests. Maybe it was the shamanic blessing the staff did upon arrival, maybe it was the moody jungle flora, but by the end of the evening a palpable sense of love & kinship permeated the air. 

The outfit: @monicabyrnemaison pulled this rare deadstock Chanel hand looped wool, then @thetenatelier draped every single eyelet to my body. Chanel velcro sandals for ample stomping + my lucky Serpenti watch.

The food: By @ixiimrestaurant, chef @luisronzon and @sommreynoso designed a 4 course tasting menu highlighting all the best ingredients of Yucatan. Under a canopy of trees, surrounded by fire, fountains and 200 year old stone walls, we indulged in canapes of corn consommé, hoja santo (sacred leaf) taquitos, sea snail ceviche, hamachi nori tostadas w/guajillo dressing, and the star of the show: ground smoked short rib w/recado negro & pickled xnipec. For dessert, a xoconusco “sour cactus” chocolate tamale followed by a sprawling dessert table on the lawn. 
 
After dinner, guests were escorted to our stargazing lounge, with a dozen cozy couches, two powerhouse telescopes, a very knowledgable astronomer, and perfectly clear views of Saturn’s rings & Jupiter’s moons (this truly blew my mind!) Flanking the starry show was a table of tarot readings, and an unreal tequila tasting curated by the experts at Chable, the home of a jawdropping 4,000+ bottle tequila collection. We were even surprised by a Jarana performance — traditional Yucatan dancers who  balance water glasses on their heads while performing. 

All this to say - being surrounded by the people who love you the most, was the most magical part (and we had actual mind blowing magic a la @dougmckenzie) 

Absolute perfect start to a weekend of pure bliss. ❤️
